net.hudup.core.alg

Class AlgAbstract

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.hudup.core.alg.AlgAbstract
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.rmi.Remote, java.util.EventListener, Alg, AlgRemote, SetupAlgListener, Exportable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    CTSManagerAbstract, DatasetParserAbstract, ExecutableAlgAbstract, MetricAbstract, RecommenderAbstract, SupportCacheAlgAbstract

    public abstract class AlgAbstract
extends java.lang.Object
implements Alg, AlgRemote
    This is abstract class of Alg interface. This abstract class gives out default implementation for some methods such as getConfig(), resetConfig() and createDefaultConfig(). It also declares the configuration variable config. Note that every Alg owns a configuration specified by DataConfig class.
    Version:
    10.0
    Author:
    Loc Nguyen

      • receivedSetup

        public void receivedSetup(SetupAlgEvent evt)
                   throws java.rmi.RemoteException
        Description copied from interface: SetupAlgListener
        The main method is to respond a setting up event issued by algorithm. As usual, evaluator receives this event and then passes it to GUI. In other words, evaluator often implements this method but any class can implement this method. In general, any class that implement this interface must implement this method to define respective tasks.
